# Modular Separation of Functionalities

Keep responsibilities isolated so changes stay local and do not create hidden coupling.

## Module Boundaries

- One module, one primary concern (UI, API client, route handler, service, data model, utility).
- Avoid mixing transport, business rules, and persistence in the same function.
- Keep route handlers thin; move reusable business logic to services.
- Keep UI components focused on rendering and interaction; move side effects to hooks/utilities.

## Dependency Direction

- Prefer: `UI -> API client -> backend route -> service -> model`.
- Do not import UI code into data/business layers.
- Share contracts via typed DTOs/interfaces instead of ad-hoc object shapes.

## Change Rules

- Add new files/modules instead of growing one large file with unrelated logic.
- If a function exceeds a single concern, split it into named helper functions.
- Reuse existing modules before duplicating logic.

## Good Practice

```text
Checkout feature:
  Dashboard handles user events only
  api/client handles HTTP + auth headers
  routes/sales validates request and delegates
  printer_service handles printing concerns only
```

## Avoid

- God files/components with mixed concerns.
- Circular imports between modules.
- Copy-pasting logic across pages/routes instead of centralizing it.
